AIM:
To create a DataFrame using pandas and perform basic data analysis and visualization using matplotlib.

Algorithm:
Start the program.
Import pandas and matplotlib libraries.
Create a dataset using dictionary format.
Convert the dataset into a DataFrame.
Display the DataFrame.
Group the data based on department.
Calculate average salary using mean().
Plot the result using bar graph.
Label the axes and title.
Display the graph.
Stop the program.

SOURCE CODE:
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as mt

data = {
    "Name": ["Arpit", "Diya", "Rohan"],
    "Age": [25, 28, 30],
    "Gender": ["M", "F", "M"],
    "City": ["Bangalore", "Mumbai", "Delhi"],
    "Salary": [50000, 60000, 75000],
    "Department": ["IT", "HR", "Finance"],
    "Experience": [2, 4, 6],
    "Joining Year": [2022, 2020, 2018],
    "Performance Rating": [3.5, 4.2, 4.8],
    "Full Time": ["Yes", "Yes", "Yes"]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)
print(df)

dept_salary = df.groupby("Department")["Salary"].mean()
print(dept_salary)

dept_salary.plot(kind="bar", color="skyblue")

mt.title("Average Salary by Department")
mt.xlabel("Department")
mt.ylabel("Average Salary")

mt.show()

